The paper deals with the problem of active learning of a hierarchical clustering using ordinal queries, which is a problem in machine learning. The paper also discusses the use of algorithms and probabilistic models to solve this problem, which are topics commonly studied in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves the use of data structures and algorithms to efficiently learn the clustering, which are topics studied in the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions applications of clustering in natural language processing and computer vision, which are areas covered by the sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
